    "it is relevant to explain brain functioning, both in healthy (e.g., vision 50, movement 51, and memory 52, 53) and in pathological (e.g., epilepsy [54] [55] [56] [57] [58] [59] [60]) conditions.",
    "We consider here an extension, with higherorder interactions, of the Kuramoto model 61, a system of coupled oscillators that has also been used to study synchronization of the brain at the cortical level [62] [63] [64].",
    "Similarly to the case of complex contagion, we also find that the nature of the transition from an incoherent to a synchronized state in the Kuramoto model can be tuned by the value of the intra-order hyperedge overlap.",
    "Namely, we switch from explosive to smooth transitions as the intra-order hyperedge overlap of the underlying hypergraph increases.",
    "Overall, our results show that, not only the presence of higher-order interactions, but also the intricate way in which they coordinate, shapes the emergence of collective behaviors in complex systems."
